  <sharedProfiles>
    <profile name="Sanctic Aegis" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="141f-c84e-6982-ba56">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">For each wound a model in your Grey Knights units is selected to suffer, roll a D6. On a 6+, that attack fails. If that unit is within 6” of a different friendly Grey Knights unit, add 1 to that roll.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Psychic Resonance" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="e371-a49c-1740-3005">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">Each of your units with Psyker X gain the following ability:

Windfall of the Warp - Cleansing Psalm: After this unit makes a Psychic Test, if that Psychic Test had two or more dice with the same result, select up to one friendly infantry or monster unit within 8” of this unit. Then, the selected unit Heals 1.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Warp Drives" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="3f2f-e0fa-470f-e498">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">After this unit is Activated in reserves, you may use ‘warp drives’. If you do, roll 3+2D6. Then, you must Deploy this unit anywhere on the battlefield at least X” away from all enemy units where X is the result of that roll. Then, this unit cannot March or Fall Back this turn.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="We Are The Hammer" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="3bfb-8d5a-08a7-a5ca">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">Reroll failed Resolve Tests made for your Grey Knights units.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Cleansing Psalm" typeId="266a-be4d-b9fa-94de" typeName="Windfall of the Warp" hidden="false" id="4b90-458f-5908-3282">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Psychic Power" typeId="9060-973c-99e9-75b4">After this unit makes a Psychic Test, if that Psychic Test had two or more dice with the same result, select up to one friendly infantry or monster unit within 8” of this unit. Then, the selected unit Heals 1.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Vanguard Beacon" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="ca9b-954c-18a6-ad4f">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">While this unit is in the battlefield, each time you use Warp Drives or Gate of Infinity for any of your other units, you may instead use ‘vanguard beacon’. If you do, Deploy that unit wholly within 2D6+2” of and visible to this unit. Then, that unit cannot March or Fall Back this turn.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
  </sharedProfiles>
</catalogue>
